1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:53,199
Don't tell me
you're heading to Skull Island too.

2
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:55,160
You two are going to Skull Island?

3
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:05,560
And what if I told you that day,
I saw the Black Coral?

4
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:06,960
Would you believe me?

5
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,439
I might lose control one day

6
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,640
and do something you'd never expect.

7
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,480
MS. SAIRUNG

8
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:35,640
Hey, wake up.

9
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,839
Yes? Okay.

10
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:40,760
I'm going to the market for a bit.
Watch the shop.

11
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:43,399
Okay, go ahead.

12
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:45,240
I'll watch the shop.

13
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,080
Hello?

14
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:03,360
Okay, okay. I'll go.
Can I take a shower first?

15
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,800
Okay, I'll hurry over.

16
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,520
What is it?

17
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,720
How many of them are going?

18
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:39,439
I'll try to find a way
to follow them from a distance

19
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:41,000
and see what they're going there for.

20
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:48,560
Can you send photos of them?

21
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,760
Oh?

22
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:03,680
This guy is...

23
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,800
Before we head into the field tomorrow,

24
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:15,199
I want both of you

25
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:18,080
to learn as much as possible
about Skull Island.

26
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:21,720
So, these books

27
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,600
will help a lot.

28
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:31,439
That's wonderful. I love reading.

29
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:32,560
Good.

30
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:35,600
I'd also like a short summary report
from both of you.

31
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:45,920
Kaimook, someone is here to see you.

32
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,280
- Me?
- Yes.

33
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,280
Go ahead.

34
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,240
Thank you.

35
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:06,040
I already know who it is.

36
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,760
It must be Win.

37
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,920
Who's Win?

38
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:14,360
He's Mook's boyfriend.

39
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:21,120
I didn't know
Ms. Kaimook already had a boyfriend.

40
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:26,159
They've liked each other
for a really long time.

41
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:29,520
But lately Win's been busy working

42
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:33,080
and hasn't had time for her,
so she got upset.

43
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,719
I bet

44
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:38,240
he's here to make up with her.

45
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:55,600
Mook.

46
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,160
Are you still mad at me?

47
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:11,480
I'm sorry.

48
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,720
I'll do anything you want.

49
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:27,760
I mean it. I'll do anything you ask.

50
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:31,760
Really?

51
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:34,919
Absolutely.

52
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:40,640
Then stay out of my life.

53
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:43,240
Don't ever show your face to me again.

54
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,280
Mook.

55
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:50,320
I hope you'll keep your word.

56
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,520
Mook.

57
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,640
Mook.

58
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:14,840
What's wrong?

59
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,920
I know this was your doing.

60
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:21,240
I'll let it go this time.

61
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:25,440
But if there's a next time,
I won't let you off.

62
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,600
Come in.

63
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,640
Please have a seat.

64
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,040
I finished my summary report.

65
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:18,680
What about Ms. Dara?

66
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,320
She's not finished yet.

67
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,160
OCEAN WASTE

68
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:33,320
If there's nothing else, please excuse me.

69
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:41,200
Kaimook.

70
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:48,160
I forgot to congratulate you.

71
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,280
Congratulate me for what?

72
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:56,280
For getting back together
with your boyfriend.

73
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:05,440
No matter what Dara told you,

74
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:08,560
Win and I are not together anymore.

75
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:15,520
For me, once it's over, it's over.

76
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,440
Thanks for telling me.

77
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,200
Yes.

78
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,880
Go home and get some rest.

79
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:32,600
We have to leave early tomorrow.

80
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,240
Okay.

81
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,160
Hey.

82
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:57,719
I'm never believing you again,
you crazy sister.

83
00:11:57,720 --> 00:12:01,319
Do you know how humiliated I was?

84
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:04,280
Mook didn't look like she wanted
to get back together with me at all.

85
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,599
Oh please, Win. You're so clueless.

86
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:12,000
That's just how women are.
Acting cold and glaring like that.

87
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:15,039
Do you know what happened after you left?

88
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:17,600
Mook cried her eyes out.

89
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,520
Are you serious?

90
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,240
Why would I lie to you?

91
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:33,160
But after what happened today,
it doesn't seem so.

92
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,600
She didn't even want to look at me.

93
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,839
You hurt her badly.

94
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:42,799
If she forgave you too easily,
she'd lose face.

95
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:45,000
If I were her, I'd act tough too.

96
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,439
Come on, Win.

97
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:55,200
Go make up with her again.
This time she'll definitely soften up.

98
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:01,000
Doesn't she have to go do fieldwork
on that island tomorrow?

99
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:03,760
I'll wait until she gets back first.

100
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:07,960
Suit yourself.

101
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:12,120
Maybe the atmosphere on the island will
make Mook fall for the guy chasing her.

102
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:15,440
Then I won't be able to help you anymore.

103
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:18,760
Oh?

104
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,720
Piak.

105
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:40,320
Take the boat out.

106
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,599
Huh? Right now?

107
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:45,080
Yes. Urgent job. Now!

108
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,520
Ugh.

109
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:06,720
Pong.

110
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:11,120
We're really far from shore already.
Are you gonna tell me where we're going?

111
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,119
To hell.

112
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,200
Hey!

113
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:27,879
Don't. No!

114
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,240
I'll kill you.

115
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,240
I'll kill you. I'll kill you.

116
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:40,679
Hey! No! Don't!

117
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:41,839
Don't hurt me!

118
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,520
- Piak!
- Help!

119
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,760
What's wrong?

120
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:53,719
What's wrong?

121
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,960
Was it just a dream?

122
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:57,040
It felt so real.

123
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:04,880
What kind of dream
makes you scream so loud?

124
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,880
I dreamed about a ghost.

125
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:15,880
What?

126
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:23,039
Guess talking about ghosts yesterday

127
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:25,359
got into my head.

128
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:27,120
That was ridiculous.

129
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:32,280
Well, if it was just a dream,
then forget it.

130
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:35,799
But it felt so real.

131
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:38,239
Enough already. Go shower.

132
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,480
Let's go eat.

133
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:42,480
- Go.
- Okay.

134
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:44,760
You scared me.

135
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,600
- Check the oxygen tank.
- Okay.

136
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:37,799
This one's full.

137
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:38,840
Okay.

138
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,559
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

139
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:44,040
I never miss.

140
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,039
Check the bag.

141
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,240
Okay.

142
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:50,880
Apart from the suit,
what else do I need to check?

143
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:59,039
You two must be workers here, right?

144
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:01,639
Hey, hey.

145
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:05,160
Watch your mouth. Pong owns this shop.

146
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:06,760
Yeah?

147
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:10,039
I want to rent a boat to Skull Island.
How much?

148
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,920
No amount of money will get us there.

149
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,040
- Why not?
- Oh?

150
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:16,078
We're closed for vacation.

151
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:18,759
Go find another shop.

152
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:20,358
I already checked.

153
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:23,719
Every other boat's rented out.
What do you want me to do?

154
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,960
Serves you right. Then don't go.

155
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:33,239
Fine. Name your price. I can pay.

156
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:35,239
Are you deaf? We said no.

157
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:36,520
Twenty thousand.

158
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:39,400
No bargaining. You going or not?

159
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:42,920
But you said you wouldn't go.

160
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:45,799
Twenty thousand. That's it.

161
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:48,799
Why the hell is it so expensive?

162
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:50,479
That's ridiculously overpriced.

163
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:52,799
Watch your mouth.

164
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,120
You going or not?

165
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:59,520
Fine. I don't have a choice anyway.

166
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:02,320
Hurry up.

167
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,200
Twenty thousand, alright?

168
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:07,280
- Prepare things for him.
- Yes, bro.

169
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:14,720
Wow.

170
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:30,920
I'm sorry.

171
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,160
It's alright.

172
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:37,280
It's only us here?

173
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:41,320
It looks like two couples
on a beach trip, doesn't it?

174
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:46,719
The staff has already left.

175
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,840
We'll meet them on the island.

176
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:56,919
Then let's take a selfie together.

177
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:58,599
It'll be a nice memory.

178
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,800
Please.

179
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:06,200
Come on.

180
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,960
One, two, three.

181
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:13,159
Closer, please.

182
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:14,720
One, two, three.

183
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:18,760
One, two, three.

184
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:26,960
You look like you're on vacation.

185
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:29,040
So different from your friend.

186
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:37,399
Let Mook take her pictures.

187
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:41,600
She's only acting busy
so she won't have to think about Win.

188
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:44,560
So they made up already?

189
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:49,320
Yep. Who knows, maybe there'll be
a surprise waiting on the island.

190
00:19:58,960 --> 00:19:59,880
The boat's ready.

191
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:02,320
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

192
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:13,199
Don't! Don't! Don't go!

193
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,360
- Don't go.
- Huh?

194
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,519
- Don't.
- What's wrong with that guy?

195
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:18,399
- No!
- Oh.

196
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:19,520
What did he say?

197
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:23,199
He's crazy. Ignore him.

198
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:24,720
Just sit down.

199
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:32,839
It's here. It's here.

200
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:35,000
Don't go. Come back!

201
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:39,480
Don't go. It's here.

202
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:57,840
Wow.

203
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:01,480
It's so beautiful.
Totally different from what I imagined.

204
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,439
I thought it'd be

205
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:06,960
some barren, lifeless island.

206
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:10,360
Right? It feels so peaceful and lush.

207
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:28,000
Hey, when will we get there?

208
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:31,320
You'll know when we get there.

209
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:34,560
Hey, why are you going to Skull Island?

210
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:36,360
To see my girlfriend.

211
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,840
What's so funny?

212
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:44,239
Hey, is your girlfriend
a monkey or something?

213
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:46,920
Piak, don't tease him.

214
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:50,639
Bro, there's nobody on that island.

215
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:53,960
The Save Sea staff
are doing field research there.

216
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:56,280
If you don't know anything, then shut up.

217
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,639
Oh.

218
00:21:58,640 --> 00:22:00,679
So you work for Save Sea too?

219
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:04,120
No. I already told you
I'm just here to see my girlfriend.

220
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:07,239
How many days
are they staying on the island?

221
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:08,999
Stop asking.

222
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,160
Just get me there. It's hot.

223
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,439
- Hello.
- Hello.

224
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,599
- Hello.
- Mr. Narathon.

225
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,160
Hello.

226
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,199
How have you been, Aunt Num?
It's been a long time.

227
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:51,279
I'm doing well. I've been preparing
the rooms for everyone.

228
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:52,679
They're not completely finished yet,

229
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:54,919
but most of it's done.

230
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:55,920
That's alright.

231
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:58,919
I'm already grateful you came to help.

232
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:01,319
How could I refuse?

233
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:03,599
I owe you a lot.

234
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:05,040
Even if I...

235
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:10,240
Even if I had other business to deal with,
I still had to make time to come.

236
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:12,759
Alright.

237
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:15,599
Then please take Ms. Kaimook

238
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:17,439
and Ms. Dara to their rooms first.

239
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:19,440
Of course. This way, please.

240
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:21,879
Let me take that.

241
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:23,160
Alright.

242
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:25,320
- Let's head to the center.
- Yeah.

243
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:26,880
Let's go.

244
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:34,399
There are only
a few people on this island.

245
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:37,400
It's almost a deserted island, ma'am.

246
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:38,920
Why?

247
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:41,559
I don't really know much
about this place myself.

248
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:43,679
I only know that

249
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:47,760
originally, some foreigners
and university professors built it.

250
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,439
Then why did they stop using it, Auntie?

251
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:54,639
Well, I don't know.

252
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:56,239
Maybe they ran out of funding.

253
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:58,239
Or maybe

254
00:23:58,240 --> 00:24:01,279
it was after that diving team died.

255
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:02,879
That probably shut the whole project down,

256
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:07,040
and everyone packed up and left.

257
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:10,319
A diving team died?

258
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:11,359
Yes.

259
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:15,120
The whole team. No survivors.

260
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:17,679
How did they die?

261
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:21,560
They went diving.

262
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,919
They disappeared for several days

263
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:26,560
before their bodies were found.

264
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:33,119
What happened to them?
How did they all die like that?

265
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:36,879
I heard something
about whirlpools or currents.

266
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,840
I don't really understand
all that technical stuff myself.

267
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:44,239
Then why did everyone living on the island
also leave?

268
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:46,759
Who could stand staying here?

269
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:48,759
One day this person sees someone,

270
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:51,319
another day someone else

271
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,960
sees something strange...

272
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:58,159
Even the construction crews they hired
would run away

273
00:24:58,160 --> 00:24:59,760
after just a few days on the island.

274
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,599
Just talking about it gives me chills.

275
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:06,920
Like right here,
someone saw something too.

276
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:14,920
- Have you ever seen it?
- Whoa.

277
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:17,159
I wouldn't stay to see anything.

278
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:21,279
When someone said they saw something,
I'd be the first to run away.

279
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:24,880
If the professor hadn't kept asking me
morning and night,

280
00:25:26,280 --> 00:25:27,960
I wouldn't have come here either.

281
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:32,720
This island is cursed.

282
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:37,360
Come on, let's get you to your room.

283
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:14,559
Hey, wait.

284
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:16,359
Stop right there.

285
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:17,280
What now?

286
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:21,120
The money?

287
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:24,040
Ugh, I'm not gonna stiff you.

288
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:30,760
Take it.

289
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:33,519
Alright. Let's head back, bro.

290
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:34,479
All good?

291
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:35,399
- Yeah.
- Alright.

292
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,640
Wait!

293
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:39,800
- What now?
- Wait.

294
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:45,719
What now? Don't tell me the money's short.

295
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,720
No.

296
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:51,439
Well, I'll wait here. In case you change
your mind and don't stay overnight.

297
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:54,560
Are you trying to squeeze
more boat money out of me?

298
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:58,080
No chance. I'm not going back yet.
You guys can leave.

299
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:01,480
I'll wait.

300
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:04,319
Wait for what? I said I'm staying.

301
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:06,840
You don't understand human language?

302
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:11,640
Why are we waiting for him?

303
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:14,480
Just stay out of it.

304
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:18,800
I don't want to stay
on this island for long.

305
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:38,600
Hello.

306
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:43,519
Auntie, this is

307
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:45,119
where the research team stays, right?

308
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:49,279
Yes.
But you aren't one of the staff, are you?

309
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:51,519
No. I'm here to see a friend.

310
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:53,400
Her name is Kaimook. Do you know her?

311
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:55,799
Ms. Kaimook.

312
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:58,799
Please wait inside. I'll call her for you.

313
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,080
Thank you so much.

314
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:29,760
Who's that?

315
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:32,599
It's me. Can I come in?

316
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:34,560
Come in. I didn't lock the door.

317
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:43,960
What's wrong?

318
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,800
Is something wrong with your room?

319
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,560
No.

320
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:01,800
Mook,

321
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:04,920
do you have a strange feeling here?

322
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:08,080
No.

323
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:14,360
Mook.

324
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,280
I have a strange feeling.

325
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:23,200
It's like this island has...

326
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:28,960
What, Da? Why are you so jumpy?

327
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:31,080
It's just someone knocking.

328
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,520
Ms. Kaimook.

329
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:36,840
Yes, ma'am?

330
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:40,920
Someone's here to see you.
He's waiting at the research center.

331
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:17,800
You can't keep running away from it.

332
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,560
Face the truth.

333
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:35,640
How is there a phone signal here?

334
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:39,520
Sairung?

335
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:45,640
Hello?

336
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:49,320
I'm on Skull Island.

337
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:53,960
I'm really here.

338
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:57,240
Video call me.

339
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:22,880
Since when
does that island have a phone signal?

340
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:26,080
Relax.

341
00:31:26,600 --> 00:31:28,080
I'm still investigating.

342
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:31,080
Did you find any leads?

343
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:34,160
Hello? Hello?

344
00:31:49,480 --> 00:31:54,680
<i>The number you have dialed
cannot be connected at the moment.</i>

345
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,640
Can he get anything done?

346
00:32:00,320 --> 00:32:01,400
Do it harder.

347
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:02,840
Yes, ma'am.

348
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,040
Useless.

349
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:17,519
- Mook.
- Sorry.

350
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:20,960
This is my workplace. It's not convenient
for us to receive visitors here.

351
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:24,759
Win came all the way here
to make up with you.

352
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:26,440
Why are you acting hard to get?

353
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:29,319
I just want some peace right now.

354
00:32:29,320 --> 00:32:32,319
The most important thing
for me right now is finishing my portfolio

355
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:34,199
so I can apply for further studies.

356
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:37,519
Mook, please hear me out.

357
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:40,959
I know you must be angry
that I followed you here.

358
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:43,359
But I want you to know

359
00:32:43,360 --> 00:32:45,800
that I really want us to clear things up

360
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:48,080
before it's too late.

361
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:50,960
I'm sorry,

362
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:53,040
but we can't really
accommodate visitors here.

363
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:56,520
This island is a research area.

364
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:59,760
Unauthorized outsiders
aren't allowed to enter freely.

365
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:05,080
Mr. Thon,

366
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:08,999
Win only came to visit Mook and me.

367
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:11,560
This isn't my private island.

368
00:33:12,360 --> 00:33:15,760
I'm responsible for the area of the island
we've been authorized to work on.

369
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:19,159
So even important business isn't allowed?

370
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,160
Correct.

371
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:22,880
You understand now, right?

372
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:28,240
I don't mean to kick you out,

373
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:30,560
but I'm going to have to ask you to leave.

374
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:37,119
The boat I hired already left.

375
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:38,920
Do you expect me to swim back?

376
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:46,400
Mr. Narathon, can our boat take him back?

377
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:50,240
I think so.

378
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:09,198
Bro.

379
00:34:09,199 --> 00:34:10,159
What?

380
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:13,839
That guy's back.

381
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:16,519
Guess his girlfriend kicked him out.

382
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:18,320
Look at him acting all suspicious.

383
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:25,119
Hey, you guys are still here?

384
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:27,519
Are you sure
you don't want me to wait for you?

385
00:34:27,520 --> 00:34:28,879
Whoa.

386
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:32,000
I said I'm staying. You can leave.

387
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:36,000
We're not leaving yet.

388
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:39,158
You're acting like this.

389
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:40,800
I bet you lied
to your girlfriend about something.

390
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,079
We're not leaving yet.

391
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:46,560
The breeze here's pretty nice.
We could sit around a little longer.

392
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:50,120
Stop talking.

393
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:53,639
I'll give you both
another 1,000 for waiting.

394
00:34:54,639 --> 00:34:58,200
Then leave.

395
00:34:58,720 --> 00:34:59,600
Take it.

396
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:01,399
Leave.

397
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:02,399
Let's head back.

398
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:03,679
- Oh?
- I've got the money.

399
00:35:03,680 --> 00:35:04,920
Go.

400
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:07,920
Why are you still here?

401
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:10,360
Go. Leave.

402
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:14,439
Let's go.

403
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:16,120
Why is it so hard for you to leave?

404
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:18,640
Let's go.

405
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:14,240
What are you looking at?

406
00:36:14,760 --> 00:36:15,880
A boat.

407
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:17,639
Whose boat?

408
00:36:17,640 --> 00:36:18,840
Pong's boat.

409
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:26,800
Dara's brother said the boat already left
after dropping him off.

410
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:30,399
I got careless.

411
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:31,960
I should have checked the pier first.

412
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:35,120
Pong's boat just left a moment ago.

413
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:37,240
What was he doing here?

414
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:38,920
I don't know.

415
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:44,240
Well, what are you going to do about him?

416
00:36:45,720 --> 00:36:47,720
I'll have the Save Sea boat take him back.

417
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:52,120
I feel bad for Kaimook.

418
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:55,199
Why?

419
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:58,040
None of this is Kaimook's fault.
I understand her.

420
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:05,519
Thanks for helping my student.

421
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:08,520
Even though you don't seem
to like her very much.

422
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:10,800
I'm going.

423
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:58,000
Mook.

424
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:01,400
Mook.

425
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:08,320
Win, I'm working.

426
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:12,920
I don't see you doing anything.
You've just been playing with that camera.

427
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:15,079
Do you really not know

428
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:18,040
or are you pretending
not to know why I'm here?

429
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:20,399
Of course, I know.

430
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:23,400
You came here for your internship.

431
00:38:25,080 --> 00:38:28,839
Then please let me work.
As for whatever you want to talk about,

432
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:32,119
we can talk once we're back in Bangkok.

433
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:33,320
Oh, Mook,

434
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:35,280
well,

435
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:37,840
you're still mad at me?

436
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:43,440
Excuse me.

437
00:38:44,560 --> 00:38:46,959
Mook, listen to me first.

438
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:47,960
I'm sorry.

439
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:50,920
Can we go back
to the way things used to be?

440
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:53,560
Mook.

441
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:01,040
Mook. Mook.

442
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:05,120
Mook.

443
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:08,680
Mook.

444
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:12,200
Please stop. Please listen to me.

445
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:22,400
Mook.

446
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,240
Mook, can you listen to me?

447
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:29,480
Go ahead. Run after each other
all around the island.

448
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:45,880
Mook. Mook.

449
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:54,160
Mook.

450
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:09,880
Kaimook.

451
00:40:12,720 --> 00:40:13,680
What are you running from?

452
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,000
Kaimook.

453
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,360
Do you need help with something?

454
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:31,280
At first, I just disliked him.

455
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:33,920
But now, I hate him.

456
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:39,000
So, at first you liked him,

457
00:40:40,080 --> 00:40:41,440
and now you hate him.

458
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:44,520
That means

459
00:40:45,280 --> 00:40:46,480
you used to like him.

460
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:51,000
I...

461
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:54,640
I...

462
00:40:56,600 --> 00:40:57,520
Kaimook.

463
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:00,400
Why are you crying?

464
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:06,960
Kaimook.

465
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:10,960
What did he do to you?

466
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:15,520
You can tell me.

467
00:41:22,240 --> 00:41:23,440
Do whatever it takes.

468
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:26,720
I don't want to see Win ever again.

469
00:41:31,200 --> 00:41:32,040
Mook.

470
00:41:37,680 --> 00:41:38,960
We need to talk.

471
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,920
She has nothing left
to say to you anymore.

472
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:45,720
I think you should
prepare to leave the island

473
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:48,640
before this turns into a bigger problem.

474
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:12,040
Win came all the way here for her.
Mook will definitely soften up.

475
00:42:12,560 --> 00:42:15,720
Good. Maybe she'll finally stop getting
in the way between me and Mr. Thon.

476
00:43:30,360 --> 00:43:31,360
Oh?

477
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:32,880
Come on.

478
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:40,200
Why did the lights go out now?

479
00:44:14,760 --> 00:44:16,960
Whether it's spirits or humans,

480
00:44:17,480 --> 00:44:18,439
it won't spare anyone.

481
00:44:18,440 --> 00:44:19,760
What do you mean by that?

482
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:22,680
What's that light?

483
00:44:32,280 --> 00:44:33,800
Get off this island!

484
00:44:34,960 --> 00:44:37,880
Is anyone out there?
Please open the door for me.

485
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:17,120
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
